==== Quick guide ====

Save this code example as Powershell file(e.g. Example.ps1) in the scripts folder.

<source>
echo %date%_%time% - This is a Powershell script>>%~dp0\Example.txt
</source>

Note: The Shell script needs into the folder: "scripts"
* Go to [[Admin:Tasks|Recurring Tasks]]
* Click '''Add Task'''
# Choose in '''Task''': ShellScriptTask
# Enter in '''Identifer''' a name(e.g. ExampleScript)
# Enter in '''Scheduler''' the time in minutes(e.g. 60)
# Enter/Choose in '''Script''' the script relative to the scripts folder (e.g. Example.ps1)
# Choose in '''Script Type''' the type of the script (e.g. Auto Detect)
# Click '''Submit'''
